Sentencas: Oxidation resistance, and the long-term stability of interconnects in solid oxide fuel cells, can be ameliorated by the use of a protective, effective, relatively dense and well adherent, spinel coating.
Titulo: Evaluation of the Parabolic Rate Constant During Different Types of Oxidation Tests for Spinel Coated Fe-17%Cr Alloy

Sentencas: In this study, the pack cementation method was employed to coat cobalt onto AISI 430 ferritic stainless steel.
Titulo: Evaluation of the Parabolic Rate Constant During Different Types of Oxidation Tests for Spinel Coated Fe-17%Cr Alloy

Sentencas: Isothermal oxidation, cyclic oxidation, and oxidation at different temperatures (600-900 degrees C) were applied to evaluate the parabolic rate constant (k(p)).
Titulo: Evaluation of the Parabolic Rate Constant During Different Types of Oxidation Tests for Spinel Coated Fe-17%Cr Alloy

Sentencas: In each test, the coated samples demonstrated lower k(p), indicating that the coating layer was effective.
Titulo: Evaluation of the Parabolic Rate Constant During Different Types of Oxidation Tests for Spinel Coated Fe-17%Cr Alloy

Sentencas: The formation of MnCo2O4 and CoCr2O4 spinels, during the oxidation, improved the oxidation resistance of AISI 430 ferritic stainless steel.
Titulo: Evaluation of the Parabolic Rate Constant During Different Types of Oxidation Tests for Spinel Coated Fe-17%Cr Alloy
